OpenEmbedded/Yocto layer for systemd-nspawn containers ( E-Con Linux Distribution)
======================================================================================

This layer provides support for tiny/minimal systemd-nspawn containers for
use with OpenEmbedded and/or Yocto layer.

This layer depends on:

URI: git://git.openembedded.org/openembedded-core
branch: hardknott
revision: HEAD

URI: git://git.openembedded.org/meta-openembedded
branch: hardknott
revision: HEAD

Contributing
------------

Please submit any patches against the `meta-econ` layer by
using the GitHub pull-request feature.  Fork the repo, make a branch,
do the work, rebase from upstream, create the pull request.

For some useful guidelines to be followed when submitting patches,
please refer to:
http://openembedded.org/wiki/Commit_Patch_Message_Guidelines

Pull requests will be discussed within the GitHub pull-request
infrastructure. If you want to get informed on new PRs and the
follow-up discussions please use GitHub's notification system.

or 

When sending single patches, please using something like:
'git send-email -1 -M --to emre.eryilmaz@piesso.com --subject-prefix=meta-econ][PATCH'

Maintainer: Emre Eryilmaz <emre.eryilmaz@piesso.com>


Source code:

    https://github.com/mofm/meta-econ
